                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY DRAPER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430130-829-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430130-829-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430130-829-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430130-cd-228" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430130-829-offence-1 t18430130-cd-228"></join>23rd of Jan</rs>., 2 pairs of boots, value 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 2 pairs of shoes, value 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18430130-name-1397" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1397" type="surname" value="BINGLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1397" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430130-829-offence-1 t18430130-name-1397"></join>Thomas Bingley</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430130-name-1398" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1398" type="surname" value="BINGLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1398" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BINGLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a boot and shoemaker, and live in Pleasant-row, Old Kent-road. I have a shop in the Park-road—the prisoner was my apprentice—I left my shop about four o'clock, on the 23rd of Jan., and re<lb></lb>turned about ten—I then found the prisoner in custody—these are my shoes and boots—the prisoner had no business with them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430130-name-1399" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1399" type="surname" value="SYMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430130-name-1399" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SYMES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a relative of the prisoner—he came to me about twenty minutes to eight o'clock, on the 23rd of Jan.—I was in bed—he asked me to come out with him—I asked where he was going—he said, "I have got some boots here to pawn"—I asked him where he got them from—he said, "I will tell you when you come out"—I put on my boots, and went out—I asked him again—he said he had taken them from his master,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184301300264"></xptr>
               <p>and wanted me to pawn them for him—I said I would have nothing to do with them, and told him to take them back—he said no, he would throw them away, if I did not like to pawn them—I said I would take him to his master's—he said, "No"—I then said I would take them from him, and have the money for him on Sunday—I sent word to his mother to come home, and we went to his master's, but could make no one hear, and came away—next morning I was coming down with them again, and the policeman took me and the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
